description.narrative: In 2021, UNICEF partnered with NGOs, the Government and appointed goodwill ambassadors advocate for children’s right, boost child participation and youth engagement. As gang-related violence developed in the metropolitan area of Port-au-Prince, HCO advocated for children to go to and come back from school in security. After the earthquake, HCO launched a back-to-school campaign for children in the affected south-west region to open school as early as possible. ;On World Children&39;s Day, it supported 200 children including children with disabilities to advocate for their rights in emergency and helped children and U-Reporters to raise awareness among communities on the radio. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:24/01/2022
